sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User (browser)
    participant API as Inbox API<br/>(JWT: tenantId from token)
    participant DB as InboxItem<br/>(DDB PK=tenant#user)
    participant CTR as unread_ctr<br/>(same DDB item)
    participant WS as WebSocket
    participant RG as ResolutionGroup

    U->>API: GET /v1/inbox (JWT)
    Note over API: tenantId from JWT — LeadingKeys IAM enforces it
    API->>DB: Query PK=tenant#user WHERE expiresAt>now AND state IN(unread,read)
    Note over DB: visibility filter: expired never returned<br/>resolved items masked until sweep lands
    DB-->>API: page of items + cursor
    API->>CTR: GET unread_ctr
    CTR-->>API: count
    API-->>U: {items, unreadCount, nextCursor}

    U->>API: POST /v1/inbox/{id}/read
    API->>DB: CondUpdate state=unread→read (condition: state=unread)
    alt transition succeeded
        DB-->>API: ok
        API->>CTR: ADD unread_ctr -1
        Note over CTR: atomic; conditional win ensures exactly one decrement
        alt type.dismissOnRead=true
            API->>DB: CondUpdate state=read→dismissed
        end
        API-->>U: 200
        API->>WS: badge update
    else already read/dismissed
        DB-->>API: ConditionalCheckFailed
        API-->>U: 200 (idempotent)
    end

    U->>API: POST /v1/inbox/{id}/resolve (A14 backup path)
    Note over API: verify item belongs to this user's tenant (LeadingKeys)
    API->>DB: GET item → verify ownership
    API->>RG: trigger group sweep
    RG->>DB: Query GSI groupKey → all items in group
    RG->>DB: BatchUpdate state=resolved × N
    RG->>CTR: ADD unread_ctr -1 × N users (conditional: was unread)
    RG->>WS: remove × N + badge updates
    API-->>U: 200
    Note over API: audit: resolved{principal:user, path:inbox, episode}
